This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
10:09 AM case called. Prosecuting Attorney Matthew Z Kirkpatrick in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Amy J Farnham not in court. State requests warrant.

Warrant ordered.
LETC - Letter to defendant with signature bond ordered in court 9/8/2022. Request to return signed bond and Affidavit of Witness form to Clerk of Court no later than 9/19/2022.

(Case called at 11:25 AM- by Zoom) No appearance by Defendant Amy Farnham. Attorney Zebulon Patek appears by video from the jail. ADA Afton Lewis appears in person for the State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant is in the Eau Claire County Jail but refuses to come out of her cell. Court notes that this is the second day the Defendant has refused to appear for Court and finds the Defendant has waived her right to a personal appearance and waived reading of the complaint. 
Settlement Conference (by phone) with District Attorney's Office (715-839-4828) on 09/28/2022 at 09/28/2022 at 2:00 PM. 
Hearing: 10/20/2022 at 9:30 AM.

Conditions:
No contact with H.F., T.L.
No acts/threats of violence toward anyone.
**Defendant was released from the jail without signing. Bond mailed to Defendant's address for signature by Clerk of Courts Office**

Case called at 11:21 AM.
Defendant Amy J Farnham in custody but does not appear.  Prosecuting Attorney Tiffany M. Winter in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Sonia Anderson appeared via video from the jail.
Attorney Anderson indicates the Defendant is refusing to appear from the jail.
Initial Appearance Adjourned to 9/8/22 at 11:00 AM.
Initial appearance scheduled for September 8, 2022 at 11:00 am.
